C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20constantly%20babies%20my%20husband%20in%20a%20way%20that%20insinuates%20I%20should%20be%20doing%20these%20things%20for%20him.%20I%20didn't%20marry%20a%20man-child%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20intention%20of%20treating%20him%20like%20one%2C%20but%20the%20longer%20she%20lives%20with%20us%2C%20the%20more%20her%20constant%20service%20is%20becoming%20his%20expectation.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBottom%20line%3A%20I%20want%20her%20out.%20The%20truth%20is%2C%20however%2C%20she%20can't%20afford%20it.%20She's%20in%20her%20mid-50s.%20I%20think%20she%20could%20support%20herself%2C%20but%20it%20would%20take%20changing%20her%20life%20by%20getting%20a%20job%2C%20getting%20job%20qualifications%2C%20being%20independent%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20She%20has%20a%20daughter%20as%20well%20as%20my%20husband%2C%20but%20her%20daughter%20has%20kids%2C%20and%20we%20don't%2C%20so%20everyone%20seems%20to%20have%20agreed%20that's%20not%20as%20good%20of%20an%20option.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20husband%20loves%20me%20and%20understands%20my%20frustration%2C%20but%20he%20would%20never%20turn%20his%20mom%20out%20on%20the%20street%2C%20which%20is%20something%20I%20love%20about%20him.%20However%2C%20I%20also%20need%20his%20mother%20out%20of%20my%20house%20immediately.%20What%20do%20I%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20Her%20Out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Get%20Her%20Out%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20thinking%20of%20ways%20you%20can%20solve%20your%20mother-in-law%2Froommate%20woes%2C%20and%20I%20landed%20on%20a%20couple%20of%20potential%20solutions.%20But%20before%20I%20dive%20into%20these%20solutions%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20talk%20about%20strategies%20for%20handling%20some%20of%20the%20complaints%20you%20listed%20in%20your%20letter.%20Remember%2C%20even%20if%20your%20mother-in-law%20leaves%20your%20house%2C%20she%20will%20still%20be%20in%20your%20lives%2C%20hip-checking%20you%20out%20of%20every%20photo%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETalk%20to%20your%20husband%20about%20his%20mother's%20behavior%20and%20how%20it%20makes%20you%20feel.%20Ask%20him%20to%20stick%20up%20for%20you%20when%20he%20sees%20her%20being%20passive-aggressive.%20This%20doesn't%20have%20to%20look%20like%20a%20grand%20call%20out%3B%20a%20simple%20%26quot%3BI'm%20the%20lucky%20one%2C%20Mom%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20she's%20insinuating%20you%20don't%20deserve%20him%20will%20do%20the%20trick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20tempting%20as%20it%20is%20to%20fight%20for%20our%20in-laws'%20approval%2C%20don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20stick%20up%20for%20yourself%20as%20well.%20Again%2C%20this%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20a%20dramatic%20showdown.%20A%20gentle%20rebuttal%20such%20as%2C%20%26quot%3BHe%20enjoys%20working%20in%20the%20kitchen%2C%26quot%3B%20if%20she's%20complaining%20about%20him%20having%20to%20cook%20for%20himself%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20always%20says%20the%20same%20about%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20if%20she's%20referring%20to%20what%20a%20catch%20her%20son%20is%2C%20should%20gracefully%20shut%20her%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20getting%20her%20out%20of%20the%20basement%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20time%20to%20reexamine%20the%20sister-in-law%20option.%20I%20understand%20she%20is%20already%20working%20with%20a%20pretty%20full%20house%2C%20but%20having%20another%20adult%20around%20to%20help%20with%20childcare%20sounds%20like%20more%20of%20an%20asset%20than%20a%20drawback.%20Of%20course%2C%20there's%20always%20the%20question%20of%20limited%20space%2C%20but%20that's%20a%20problem%20a%20little%20rearranging%20can%20likely%20fix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsking%20kids%20to%20share%20a%20bedroom%20or%20your%20mother-in-law%20to%20sleep%20on%20a%20futon%20might%20be%20a%20big%20ask%2C%20but%20so%20is%20asking%20you%20and%20your%20husband%20to%20shoulder%20your%20mother-in-law's%20challenging%20circumstances%20alone.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20also%20a%20lot%20to%20ask%20of%20your%20sister-in-law%20and%20her%20family%20to%20carry%20alone%2C%20so%20I%20suggest%20you%20all%20consider%20taking%20turns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20your%20mother-in-law%20alternate%20spending%20a%20month%20living%20at%20your%20place%20and%20your%20husband's%20sister's%20place.%20This%20will%20give%20everyone%20much-needed%20breaks%20from%20one%20another.%20And%20while%20it%20won't%20give%20your%20mother-in-law%20a%20lot%20of%20permanence%2C%20permanence%20probably%20isn't%20the%20best%20way%20to%20achieve%20forward%20momentum%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20second%20solution%20is%20for%20you%20to%20talk%20to%20your%20husband%20about%20an%20exit%20plan.%20This%20is%20very%20different%20than%20telling%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BThrow%20your%20mother%20out%20on%20the%20streets.%20I've%20had%20it!%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20tell%20him%20that%20you%20don't%20feel%20like%20this%20is%20a%20long-term%20solution%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20abandon%20the%20woman%20who%20raised%20him%20in%20her%20time%20of%20need%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20you'd%20like%20to%20sit%20down%20together%20and%20devise%20an%20action%20plan%20for%20getting%20her%20back%20on%20her%20feet.%20Talk%20about%20strategies%20for%20helping%20her%20rejoin%20the%20workforce%20and%20start%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fhow-to-save-money%5C%22%3Esave%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Real%20estate%20licensing%20can%20be%20an%20excellent%20option%20for%20a%20third%20act.%20She%20could%20look%20into%20becoming%20a%20substitute%20teacher%20or%20starting%20a%20small%20business%20like%20being%20a%20doula%2C%20caterer%2C%20or%20dog%20walker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20mother-in-law%20is%20still%20a%20few%20years%20away%20from%20collecting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20qualifying%20for%20Medicare%2C%20but%20help%20her%20look%20into%20other%20assistance%20programs%20that%20might%20help%2C%20such%20as%20subsidized%20housing%20or%20SNAP.%20You%20mentioned%20she%20made%20financial%20mistakes%20previously%2C%20so%20helping%20her%20find%20ways%20to%20rebuild%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fwhat-is-an-excellent-credit-score%5C%22%3Ecredit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20also%20be%20extremely%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemind%20your%20husband%20that%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20other%20ways%20to%20help%20his%20mother%20beyond%20giving%20her%20a%20place%20to%20stay.%20Not%20only%20will%20she%20likely%20prefer%20independence%20in%20her%20own%20place%2C%20but%20she'll%20also%20have%20security%20knowing%20she%20has%20such%20a%20strong%20support%20system%20nearby%20cheering%20her%20on.%20Just%2C%20you%20know%2C%20not%20right%20upstairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERooting%20for%20all%20of%20you%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELooking%20for%20advice%20on%20how%20your%20savings%2C%20debt%2C%20or%20another%20financial%20challenge%20is%20affecting%20your%20relationships%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20adviso