sider.com%2F66a25d842d66759f66fe353f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexandra%20Saville%20(not%20pictured)%20never%20wanted%20kids%20but%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20much%20she%20enjoyed%20having%20a%20relationship%20with%20her%20partner's%20son.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20always%20planned%20on%20remaining%20child-free%2C%20and%20then%20I%20started%20dating%20someone%20with%20a%20child.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20has%20helped%20me%20realize%20there%20are%20so%20many%20unique%20ways%20to%20be%20a%20family.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOvercoming%20other%20people's%20inability%20to%20understand%20our%20dynamic%20has%20been%20a%20challenge.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20don't%20remember%20officially%20deciding%20that%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildless-marriage-no-regret-stepkids-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edidn't%20want%20children%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20wasn't%20so%20much%20a%20decision%20as%20a%20universal%20truth%20hidden%20somewhere%20deep%20in%20my%20gut.%20Somewhere%20along%20the%20way%2C%20it%20moved%20from%20preference%20to%20certainty%2C%20from%20decision%20to%20fact.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%20signs.%20When%20I%20was%20young%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20dolls%20and%20babysat%20only%20once.%20I%20didn't%20play%20house.%20I%20loved%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelped-raise-siblings-dont-want-kids-child-free-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20younger%20siblings%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fiercely%20%E2%80%94%20maternally%2C%20even%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20was%20specific%20to%20them%20and%20non-transferable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20many%20people%20describe%20motherhood%20as%20their%20calling%20that%20we%20sometimes%20forget%20it's%20not%20that%20way%20for%20everyone%3B%20it's%20actually%20a%20very%20personal%20choice.%20It's%20one%20of%20many%20possible%20paths%20%E2%80%94%20a%20'maybe%2C'%20not%20an%20inevitability%2C%20and%20I%20always%20knew%20it%20was%20a%20'no'%20for%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%2C%20I%20fell%20for%20someone%20who%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parent-dating-tips-easier-transition-for-child-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealready%20had%20a%20son%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20a%20previous%20marriage.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20our%20relationship%2C%20the%20fact%20he%20had%20a%20child%20ended%20up%20on%20the%20'con'%20side%20of%20my%20list%2C%20but%20we%20decided%20to%20go%20slow%20and%20wait%20a%20year%20before%20making%20the%20introduction%20to%20his%20son%2C%20who%20he%20had%20half%20of%20the%20time.%20We%20wanted%20to%20be%20cautious%20and%20avoid%20any%20potential%20heartache%20and%20confusion%20for%20all%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20giving%20it%20a%20year%2C%20we%20decided%20we'd%20introduce%20me%20to%20his%20son%20and%20integrate%20each%20other%20more%20into%20each%20other's%20daily%20routines%20over%20time.%20We%20also%20realized%20what%20works%20for%20our%20relationship%20might%20differ%20from%20what%20works%20for%20the%20people%2C%20and%20we%20opted%20not%20to%20get%20married%20or%20combine%20households.%20I%20expected%20spending%20so%20much%20time%20in%20a%20family%20unit%20I%20didn't%20create%20would%20be%20hard.%20After%20all%2C%20I've%20never%20really%20been%20a%20kid%20person.%20And%20it%20was%2C%20but%20in%20a%20different%20way%20than%20I%20expected.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bc71504c-7fb6-443d-96b2-7ee2db15cb0b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20quickly%20formed%20a%20bond%20with%20my%20partner's%20son%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20son%20and%20I%20fell%20into%20a%20surprisingly%20easy%20groove.%20Sure%2C%20there%20were%20learning%20curves%20and%20adjustments%20and%20a%20need%20to%20overcome%20my%20aversion%20to%20animated%20movies%20and%20sticky%20surfaces.%20But%20I%20really%20loved%20our%20dynamic.%20Now%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteenage-son-first-girlfriend-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe's%20a%20teenager%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20I've%20known%20him%20for%20over%20half%20his%20life.%20We%20have%20holiday%20traditions%20and%20movie%20nights.%20We%20both%20like%20the%20beach%2C%20dogs%2C%20and%20cooking%20together.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20never%20wanted%20one%20and%20still%20don't%2C%20but%20what%20I%20do%20want%20is%20exactly%20what%20we%20have.%20It's%20not%20parenting%20necessarily%2C%20but%20it's%20something.%20It's%20caring.%20Am%20I%20called%20%26quot%3BMom%26quot%3B%3F%20No.%20Did%20I%20physically%20have%20a%20child%20or%20legally%20adopt%20one%3F%20No.%20There's%20no%20legal%20document%20connecting%20me%20to%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20do%20things%20like%20help%20with%20homework%20and%20talk%20to%20him%20about%20school%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20at%20parent-teacher%20conferences.%20I%20worry%20about%20his%20well-being%2C%20safety%2C%20and%20happiness%2C%20and%20I%20know%20I'm%20one%20of%20three%20adults%20he'd%20turn%20to%20if%20he%20needed%20support.%20And%20that%20counts%20for%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2275487664-c7c5-41a4-b0a7-4aee5aa5c88c%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20people%20sometimes%20minimize%20our%20relationship%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20I%20didn't%20expect%20was%20how%20much%20I%20would%20enjoy%20this%20role%20despite%20its%20unconventionality.%20When%20people%20ask%20if%20I%20have%20kids%2C%20I%20say%20no.%20It's%20technically%20honest%20but%20not%20entirely%20true%20because%20it%20lacks%20the%20nuance%20that%20gives%20the%20full%20picture%20of%20my%20life%20%E2%80%94%20and