0he%20created%20%26quot%3Ba%20PAC%20that%20is%20focused%20on%20supporting%20candidates%20who%20favor%20a%20meritocracy%20and%20personal%20freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20eye-popping%20donations%20aren't%20happening%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20would%20even%20be%20possible%20raised%20renewed%20concerns%20over%20big%20money's%20role%20in%20US%20elections%20%E2%80%94%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20political%20spectrum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222ada5c1-f7f6-4af7-bcfa-a6b908abfadf%5C%22%3EDemocracy%20for%20sale%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Weiner%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Brennan%20Center's%20Elections%20and%20Government%20Program%2C%20said%20mega%20donations%20from%20billionaires%20in%20recent%20election%20cycles%20underscore%20the%20pressing%20need%20for%20campaign%20finance%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20extreme%20mega-donors%20in%20past%20election%20cycles%20as%20well%2C%20but%20it's%20definitely%20supercharged%20this%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20also%20Democratic%20super%20PACs%20and%20Democratic%20mega-donors%2C%20and%20those%20donors%20have%20been%20very%20involved%20recently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%20financing%20%26quot%3Barms%20race%26quot%3B%20was%20ignited%20in%202008%20when%20then-presidential%20candidate%20Barack%20Obama%20declined%20to%20use%20the%20federal%20public%20financing%20system%2C%20which%20provides%20public%20money%20but%20with%20expenditure%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20decision%20by%20President%20Obama%20pretty%20much%20spelled%20the%20end%20of%20public%20financing%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20of%20the%20public%20finance%20system%2C%20which%20still%20exists%20but%20isn't%20widely%20used%2C%20might%20have%20been%20inevitable%20because%20it%20%26quot%3Bjust%20wasn't%20designed%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20exponentially%20greater%20campaign%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%202010%20Citizens%20United%20decision%20gave%20super%20PACs%20carte%20blanche%20to%20donate%20however%20much%20they%20wanted%20to%20support%20their%20chosen%20campaigns%20as%20long%20as%20they%20weren't%20directly%20collaborating%20with%20them.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20existing%20rules%20governing%20contact%20between%20super%20PACs%20and%20candidates%20are%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20porous%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bgo%20largely%20unenforced%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20super%20PACs%20can%20raise%20unlimited%20amounts%20of%20money%20from%20corporations%20%E2%80%94%20or%20more%20often%2C%20oligarchs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20they%20can%20turn%20around%20and%20spend%20that%20money%20for%20the%20candidate's%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20court%20engaged%20in%20this%20fiction%20that%20those%20massive%20contributions%20were%20just%20not%20really%20posing%20any%20risk%20of%20corruption%20because%20independent%20spending%20wouldn't%20be%20that%20valuable%20to%20candidates.%20But%20practically%20speaking%2C%20we%20know%20that's%20just%20not%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20United%20States%20ended%20up%20with%20high-priced%20elections%20like%20the%20one%20it's%20in%20now%20and%20the%202022%20midterms%20when%20tech%20mogul%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeter-thiel-jd-vance-veep-trump-election-kingmaker-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeter%20Thiel%20donated%20millions%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20JD%20Vance's%20campaign%2C%20Weiner%20said.%20Overall%2C%20the%20system%20%26quot%3Bleads%20to%20some%20very%20perverse%20incentives%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bdominated%20by%20these%20incredibly%20eccentric%20tech%20billionaires%20who%20get%20to%20use%20super%20PACs%20to%20have%20inordinate%20clout%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff05d96c-1edb-4318-8bee-7e8e3545e1de%5C%22%3ECampaign%20finance%20needs%20a%20bipartisan%20solution%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20change%20to%20the%20system%20would%20likely%20have%20to%20be%20legislative%20since%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20unlikely%20to%20revisit%20Citizens%20United%2C%20Weiner%20said.%20That%20means%20both%20parties%20would%20have%20to%20get%20mad%20enough%20about%20billionaires%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Einserting%20themselves%20into%20elections%20to%20collaborate%20on%20passing%20a%20legislative%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20collaboration%20hasn't%20happened%20yet.%20Democrats%20have%20twice%20introduced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-in-the-john-lewis-voting-rights-advancement-act-explainer-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFreedom%20to%20Vote%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20have%20included%20campaign%20finance%20reforms%20and%20was%20widely%20considered%20pro-voter.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreedom-to-vote-act-john-lewis-voting-rights-bill-explainer-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublicans%20blocked%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20bill%20and%20later%20proposed%20the%20American%20Confidence%20in%20Elections%20Act%2C%20which%20a%202023%20Brennan%20Center%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennancenter.org%2Four-work%2Fanalysis-opinion%2Fmany-problems-gop-backed-voting-bill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20would%20%26quot%3Bimpose%20unnecessary%20restrictions%20on%20voting%20rights%20and%20election%20administration%20nationwide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20billionaires%20ruling%20the%20day%2C%20that%20leaves%20voters%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20unhappy%26quot%3B%20with%20their%20electoral%20system%20and%20politicians%20facing%20an%20uphill%20battle%20knowing%20that%20any%20effort%20to%20strengthen%20democracy%20won't%20be%20taken%20seriously%20%26quot%3Bunless%20it%20includes%20a%20very%20strong%20campaign%20finance%20reform%20component.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that's%20interesting%20is%20that%20anger%20around%20money%20and%20politics%20crosses%20partisan%20lines%20in%20a%20way%20that%20few%20other%20democracy%20issues%20do%2C%20right%3F%20You%20have%20very%20conservative%20people%20who%20may%20not%20agree%20with%20progressives%20on%20much%20else%2C%20but%20they%20agree%20that%20the%20role%20of%20having%20oligarchs%20dominating%20our%20campaigns%20is%20a%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20does%20make%20me%20think%20that%2C%20at%20some%20point%2C%20you%20are%20going%20to%20see%20some%20pretty%20significant%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-trump-donation-campaign-finance-reform-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722159122000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669d297a80d4d5da13d5a496%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-trump-donation-campaign-finance-reform-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20if%20Musk's%20huge%20donations%20aren't%20happening%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20would%20even%20be%20possible%20raised%20renewed%20concern%20with%20big%20money's%20role%20in%20US%20elections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbalevic%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Balevic)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-trump-donation-campaign-finance-reform-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Signs%20Israel%20not%20expecting%20imminent%20escalation%20despite%20significant%20strikes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722158700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F07%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-golan-heights-lebanon_6641215.jpg%3F20240728103944%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.co